io.oasp.module.service.common.impl.discovery

Class ServiceDiscovererImplConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.oasp.module.service.common.impl.discovery.ServiceDiscovererImplConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceDiscoverer, EventListener, org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener<org.springframework.boot.context.embedded.EmbeddedServletContainerInitializedEvent>

    public class ServiceDiscovererImplConfig
extends Object
implements ServiceDiscoverer, org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener<org.springframework.boot.context.embedded.EmbeddedServletContainerInitializedEvent>
    A simple implementation of ServiceDiscoverer that is using ServiceConfig. The Service URL can be configured per application providing the service as well as statically for all services (e.g. in case of a central API gateway or a local proxy like Envoy Sidecar Proxy).
    Since:
    3.0.0
    See Also:
    ServiceConfigProperties

      • discover

        public void discover(ServiceDiscoveryContext<?> context)
        Specified by:
        discover in interface ServiceDiscoverer
        Parameters:
        context - the ServiceDiscoveryContext where to set the discovered configuration. At least the URL has to be discovered.
        It is possible to have multiple implementations of this interface as spring beans in your context. An implementation may decide that it is not responsible for the given service API (e.g. only responsible for REST services). In that case it can return without doing any modifications to the given ServiceDiscoveryContext. Until the URL has not been discovered further implementations of this interface will be invoked. If all implementations have been invoked without discovering the URL, discovery will fail with a runtime exception causing the ServiceClientFactory to fail.
